# Notifications System

Notifications drive engagement and consistency in LexMastery.

They must be helpful, not intrusive.

---

# Product Vision

Notifications must:

- improve study consistency
- remind users intelligently
- avoid notification fatigue
- support personalization
- align with learning goals

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

NotificationsController (Riverpod)

↓

NotificationsState

↓

NotificationsRepository

↓

Push Notification Service

---

# State Management

NotificationsState includes:

- loading
- synced
- scheduled
- error

Core Data:

- notificationQueue
- preferences
- deliveryStatus
- history

---

# Notification Types

- Study reminders
- AI suggestions
- Exam countdown alerts
- Streak reminders
- Course updates

---

# Scheduling Logic

Notifications must be:

- time-zone aware
- user-preference driven
- AI optimized based on study habits

---

# AI Integration

AI determines:

- best notification timing
- frequency optimization
- content personalization

---

# Offline Behaviour

- scheduling works offline
- syncs when online
- queue persists locally

---

# API Contracts

GET /notifications

POST /notifications/schedule

POST /notifications/update

DELETE /notifications/remove

---

# Analytics Events

notification_received

notification_clicked

notification_dismissed

notification_scheduled

---

# UI Composition Rules

Notification UI must include:

- list view
- grouping by type
- toggle controls
- scheduling preferences

---

# UX Rules

- never spam user
- prioritize relevance
- allow full control over frequency

---

# Error Handling

- retry delivery silently
- fallback to local scheduling

---

# Performance

- low battery impact
- minimal background processing

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- readable notification previews
- screen reader support
- vibration control options

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Scheduling logic

Notification filtering

Preference handling

Widget Tests:

Notification list

Preference UI

Integration Tests:

Push delivery flow

Scheduling accuracy

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating notifications:

- always respect user preferences
- always optimize timing using AI
- never exceed user-defined frequency limits
- always allow full opt-out